### CHECK 8 — Verify Outbound HTTP is Permitted from Plugin Sandbox

This verifies that your plugin can call the Dataverse Search API endpoint from within the plugin sandbox (needed for fuzzy search in Phase 2).

**Method:** In Dataverse online (cloud), all plugins run in **Sandbox (partial trust)** mode. Sandbox plugins **CAN** make outbound HTTP calls, subject to the following:

| Call Target | Permitted in Sandbox? |
|---|---|
| Same-org Dataverse endpoint (`[org].crm.dynamics.com/api/data/...`) | ✅ Yes — same-org calls are always permitted |
| External internet URLs | ⚠️ Requires allow-listing in some enterprise environments |
| SharePoint, Azure services | ⚠️ Depends on environment network policy |

**How to verify:**

```
Path: Admin Center → Environments → [Your Env] → Settings →
      Network Access → Allowed Domains
```

Check if there is a **restrictive allowed-domains policy**. If the field is empty or set to allow-all, outbound calls work. If there is a whitelist, ensure `[yourorg].crm.dynamics.com` is included (it usually is by default for same-org calls).

✅ **Pass:** No restrictive domain policy, or your org URL is in the list
❌ **Fail:** Add `[yourorg].crm.dynamics.com` to the allowed domains, or contact your network/security team

